n construction methods and user participation. Its design strategies, combined with state-of-the-art planning tools and research findings, look ahead to a climate-positive future. The book gives detailed information on the concepts behind Robust Architecture and Low-Tech Design. It illuminates various strategies and demonstrates how they can be easily implemented. Examples of realised projects with very different demands and requirement profiles show how straightforward robust building can be.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSustainable architecturexDesign and construction. 7aARCHITECTURE / Sustainability & Green Design.2bisacsh  arobust architecture.1 aAuer, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBertino, Gaetano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaselsteiner, Edeltraud, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaselsteiner, Edeltraud, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKisser, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlinge, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLipp, Bernhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMuñoz-Czerny, Ute, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNegelein, Bertram von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoswag-Klinge, Eike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchneider, Ursula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchöberl, Helmut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWirth, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZelger, Thomas, econtributor.